The paper discusses power indices, which are commonly used in game theory (cs.GT) and social choice theory (cs.DS). The discussion of criteria for qualifying power indices for applications involves topics such as fairness, efficiency, and computational complexity, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social influence (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of power indices in multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
